title: Grateful Dead Live at Keifer Lakefront Arena on 1988-10-18
description:
Set 1

Hell In A Bucket, They Love Each Other, Little Red Rooster, Loser, Beat It On Down The Line-> Greatest Story Ever Told, Peggy-O, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Bird Song

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums*-> Space-> I Will Take You Home-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: Iko Iko**, Knockin' On Heaven's Door**

Other Artist(s): *w/ members of Neville Brothers, ** w/ the Bangles

reviews.review_text:
Allright show. This is a nice-sounding source.  I always try to write my review on the same source as the "bread crumb" idiot who has polluted so many comments sections with his own useless personal show-listening-tracking system that becomes apparently a part of the permanent record about whatever archive.org pages he chooses to vandalize with his little "calling card" ...

Anyway, middle-of-the-pack 1988 show. Jerry's voice is mostly solid; the laryngitis really doesn't come out to play much here. First set has more energy than the second, although about halfway through "Estimated", things really heat up. That's worth a listen. I don't necessarily pay close attention to the drummers in the middle of the song part of this song, but they are REALLY going bananas here during the "I'll call down thunder..." passage particularly. 

Probably like the breadcrumbs dude, best to spin this show once and then, I guess, fly away. As he evidently does, and has done here ...

Buried in the Louisiana Country oh! Well, I went to Miami and St Pete but then left tour to see family in Sarasota. 
I remember singing El Paso to my Dad & Step-Mom 
and she set me straight on the line
"I picked a good one , looked like it could run"
no idea what I thought it was at the time.

Good to hear this show! Nice Audio..
I felt like the Dead were giving a decent show every night by this time after much of 87/88 being comeback and Dylan project
Nothing earth shattering here but not too shabby either.
BIODTL>GREATEST nice change from the cowboy double shot
(You know in N.Y.C we had much graffiti 
most of it served very little purpose 
but it was important to some people 
and despised by others) 
BUT THE ONE THING WE NEED IS
 A LEFT HAND MONKEY WRENCH 😇
First big jam of the night is in the Bird Song 

SCARLET>FIRE,ESTIMATED>EYES --always worthwhile
(Jerry has been doing some creative lyrics of his own this night)
Estimated has some nice space jams in the mix
headed into EOTW

The encores are good for the guest rarities collection.
